{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"XRInputSourcesChangeEvent","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebXR_Device_API\">WebXR Device API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent\"><code>XRInputSourcesChangeEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent\"><code>XRInputSourcesChangeEvent()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/added\"><code>added</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/removed\"><code>removed</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/session\"><code>session</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for WebXR Device API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/xr\"><code>Navigator.xr</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGLRenderingContext/makeXRCompatible\"><code>WebGLRenderingContext.makeXRCompatible()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRAnchor\"><code>XRAnchor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRBoundedReferenceSpace\"><code>XRBoundedReferenceSpace</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRCPUDepthInformation\"><code>XRCPUDepthInformation</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRDepthInformation\"><code>XRDepthInformation</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRFrame\"><code>XRFrame</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSource\"><code>XRInputSource</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourceArray\"><code>XRInputSourceArray</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourceEvent\"><code>XRInputSourceEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRPose\"><code>XRPose</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRReferenceSpace\"><code>XRReferenceSpace</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRReferenceSpaceEvent\"><code>XRReferenceSpaceEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRRenderState\"><code>XRRenderState</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRRigidTransform\"><code>XRRigidTransform</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSession\"><code>XRSession</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSessionEvent\"><code>XRSessionEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSpace\"><code>XRSpace</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSystem\"><code>XRSystem</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRView\"><code>XRView</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRViewerPose\"><code>XRViewerPose</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRViewport\"><code>XRViewport</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRWebGLBinding\"><code>XRWebGLBinding</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRWebGLDepthInformation\"><code>XRWebGLDepthInformation</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRWebGLLayer\"><code>XRWebGLLayer</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The WebXR Device API interface <strong><code>XRInputSourcesChangeEvent</code></strong> is used to represent the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSession/inputsourceschange_event\" title=\"inputsourceschange\"><code>inputsourceschange</code></a> event sent to an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSession\"><code>XRSession</code></a> when the set of available WebXR input controllers changes.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"75\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"37.5\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      Event\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"75\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"105\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"75,14 85,9 85,19 75,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"105\" y=\"0\" width=\"200\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"205\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      XRInputSourcesChangeEvent\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"constructor","title":"Constructor","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"xrinputsourceschangeevent\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent\" title=\"XRInputSourcesChangeEvent()\"><code>XRInputSourcesChangeEvent()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Creates and returns a new <code>XRInputSourcesChangeEvent</code> object. The specified type must be <code>inputsourceschange</code>, which is the only event that uses this interface.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"added\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/added\" title=\"added\"><code>added</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An array of zero or more <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSource\"><code>XRInputSource</code></a> objects, each representing an input device which has been newly connected or enabled for use.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"removed\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/removed\" title=\"removed\"><code>removed</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An array of zero or more <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSource\"><code>XRInputSource</code></a> objects representing the input devices newly connected or enabled for use.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"session\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/session\" title=\"session\"><code>session</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSession\"><code>XRSession</code></a> to which this input source change event is being directed.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>While <code>XRInputSourcesChangeEvent</code> defines no methods of its own, it inherits methods from its parent interface, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"event_types","title":"Event types","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"inputsourceschange\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSession/inputsourceschange_event\" title=\"inputsourceschange\"><code>inputsourceschange</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Delivered to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSession\"><code>XRSession</code></a> when the set of input devices available to it changes.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following example shows how to set up an event handler which uses <code>inputsourceschange</code> events to detect newly-available pointing devices and to load their models in preparation to display them in the next animation frame.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>xrSession<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"inputsourceschange\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> onInputSourcesChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">onInputSourcesChange</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">event</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> input <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> event<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>added<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>input<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>targetRayMode <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"tracked-pointer\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token function\">loadControllerMesh</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>input<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>You can also add a handler for <code>inputsourceschange</code> events by setting the <code>oninputsourceschange</code> event handler:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>xrSession<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>oninputsourceschange <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> onInputSourcesChange<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://immersive-web.github.io/webxr/#xrinputsourceschangeevent-interface","title":"WebXR Device API"}],"query":"api.XRInputSourcesChangeEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.XRInputSourcesChangeEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Constructor","id":"constructor"},{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Event types","id":"event_types"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The WebXR Device API interface XRInputSourcesChangeEvent is used to represent the inputsourceschange event sent to an XRSession when the set of available WebXR input controllers changes.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:23:40.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/xrinputsourceschangeevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/xrinputsourceschangeevent/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/073f70e052ff92ab715df3c20678c11c9b51747f","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSourcesChangeEvent","title":"XRInputSourcesChangeEvent"}],"pageTitle":"XRInputSourcesChangeEvent - 